                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On the evening of October 25, shortly after his return from Paris, Secretary of
                    State <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">Dulles</persName> presented a report on
                    the outcome of the Four-Power, Nine-Power, and North Atlantic Council meetings
                    to President <persName corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1">Eisenhower</persName> and the
                    Cabinet. This was the first open session of the Cabinet during the <persName
                        corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1">Eisenhower</persName> Administration in which
                    national press, radio, and television coverage was allowed. For information
                    concerning this Cabinet meeting, see the Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                        >Bulletin</hi>, November 8, 1954, page 677; the text of <persName
                        corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">Dulles</persName>’ remarks and the question period
                    that followed is in Department of State file 396.1 GE/3–2354.</p>
            </div>
